cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about depth estimation from monocular images using a novel self-supervised framework. This is a computer vision task, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a fully differential patch-based cost function and a parallel network for confidence map learning and estimation, which involves machine learning techniques. Therefore, the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The proposed method is evaluated on the KITTI dataset, which is a popular benchmark for autonomous driving and robotics, indicating that the paper may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
